<body>
    <main>
    <!-- FAQ Hero Section -->
    <section class="page-hero bg-primary text-white">
      <div class="container py-5">
        <div class="row py-5">
          <div class="col-lg-8">
            <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
            <p class="lead">Find answers to the most common questions about our Work & Travel USA program.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ Accordion -->
  <section class="faq-content py-5">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="mb-4">Program Requirements</h2>
      <div class="accordion" id="accordionProgram">
        <div class="accordion-item">
          <h2 class="accordion-header">
            <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">
              Who is eligible for the Work & Travel USA program?
            </button>
          </h2>
          <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" data-bs-parent="#accordionProgram">
            <div class="accordion-body">
              <p>The Work & Travel USA program is designed for full-time university students who are at least 18 years old. Participants must:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Be currently enrolled in an accredited university or college</li>
                <li>Have completed at least one semester of studies</li>
                <li>Have a good academic standing</li>
                <li>Have sufficient English language proficiency</li>
                <li>Be able to work in the USA during their summer vacation period</li>
              </ul>
              <p>Recent graduates may also be eligible if they apply before graduation.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-item">
          <h2 class="accordion-header">
            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
              What documents do I need to apply?
            </button>
          </h2>
          <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionProgram">
            <div class="accordion-body">
              <p>To apply for the Work & Travel USA program, you will need to provide:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Valid passport (valid for at least 6 months beyond your program end date)</li>
                <li>University/college enrollment verification</li>
                <li>Academic transcript</li>
                <li>CV/Resume in English</li>
                <li>Passport-sized photos</li>
                <li>Proof of English language proficiency (may be assessed during interview)</li>
                <li>Application form and program fee</li>
              </ul>
              <p>Additional documents may be required for the visa application process.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="mb-4 mt-5">Travel & Accommodation</h2>
      <div class="accordion" id="accordionTravel">
        <div class="accordion-item">
          <h2 class="accordion-header">
            <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseThree">
              Will my accommodation be provided?
            </button>
          </h2>
          <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" data-bs-parent="#accordionTravel">
            <div class="accordion-body">
              <p>Accommodation is not typically provided by the employer. However, we assist participants in finding suitable housing options near their job location. It is recommended to secure housing before arrival in the USA, but we provide resources and support during the search process.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-item">
          <h2 class="accordion-header">
            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFour">
              Can I travel during my program?
            </button>
          </h2>
          <div id="collapseFour" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionTravel">
            <div class="accordion-body">
              <p>Yes! During your Work & Travel USA program, you can travel within the USA during your off-time, but it’s important to follow the terms of your visa. Some participants travel after completing their work placement, while others may travel in between work shifts. Always check with your employer and program coordinator before making travel plans.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="mb-4 mt-5">Jobs & Placement</h2>
      <div class="accordion" id="accordionJobs">
        <div class="accordion-item">
          <h2 class="accordion-header">
            <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFive" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseFive">
              How do I get placed in a job?
            </button>
          </h2>
          <div id="collapseFive" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" data-bs-parent="#accordionJobs">
            <div class="accordion-body">
              <p>Our team will assist you in finding a suitable job based on your preferences, skills, and location availability. We work with a variety of employers across the USA who are looking to hire international students for seasonal positions. You will be required to submit your resume and go through an interview process for job matching.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-item">
          <h2 class="accordion-header">
            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseSix" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseSix">
              What kind of jobs can I apply for?
            </button>
          </h2>
          <div id="collapseSix" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionJobs">
            <div class="accordion-body">
              <p>Jobs available in the Work & Travel USA program typically include positions in hospitality, retail, food service, amusement parks, and resorts. Some examples are hotel staff, lifeguards, waitstaff, and retail associates. The job opportunities will vary based on the location and employer availability.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


